 <P><H2>Lecture Summary</H2>
</P>
<P><UL><LI>The �software crisis� or the �software challenge�<UL><LI>Studies show that software is expensive, faulty, unused, unusable, dominated by maintenance<LI>Software requirements are rapidly outpacing software technology</UL><LI>Software engineering is <UL><LI>the ability to consistently fashion software to solve appropriate problems in an orderly, predictable manner<LI>An approach to the overall problem<LI>Techniques to apply in each area of the approach</UL></UL></P>
